"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802558","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-12-15","<p>The government is committed to planting 11 million trees and to plant 1 million urban trees in England.</p><p> </p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2017-12-15T12:10:30.327Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802558/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802558/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802558/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-12-07","Tree Planting","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what targets his Department has set for tree planting.","false","Biography information for Dr David Drew","Stroud","Dr David Drew","118108"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802559","Women and Equalities","false","2017-12-12","<p>The government is determined to close the gender pay gap, which is currently at 18.4%. Research commissioned by the Government Equalities Office indicates that the biggest driver of the gender pay gap is women’s reduced labour market participation.</p><p>The research can be accessed here: <a href="https://www.research.manchester.ac.uk/portal/files/33083313/FULL_TEXT.PDF" target="_blank">https://www.research.manchester.ac.uk/portal/files/33083313/FULL_TEXT.PDF</a>.</p>","Guildford","Anne Milton","118110","2017-12-12T15:50:45.76Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802559/answer","Biography information for Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802559/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802559/answer",,,,,"31","Women and Equalities","Women and Equalities","2017-12-07","Equal Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for Women and Equalities, what assessment the Government has made of the principal reasons for the current size of the gender wage gap.","false","Biography information for Mr Peter Bone","Wellingborough","Mr Peter Bone","118109"
