"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802561","Department for International Development","false","2017-12-12","<p>No UK aid is used for payments to Palestinian prisoners or their families. UK financial assistance to the Palestinian Authority is only used to help to pay the salaries of health and education public servants in the West Bank. Only named public servants from a pre-approved EU list are eligible and a robust verification system validates that funds are used for the intended purposes. The UK government strongly condemns all forms of violence and incitement to violence.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2017-12-12T15:58:31.42Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802561/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802561/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802561/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-12-07","Palestinians: Terrorism","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, pursuant to the Memorandum of Understanding between the Palestinian Authority (PA) and her Department, what discussions her Department has had with the PA on the payment of a salary of 2,600 shekels each month for life to the family of Nimr Mahmoud Ahmed Al-Jamal who carried out the Har Adar terrorist attack on 26 September 2017.","true","Biography information for Joan Ryan","Enfield North","Joan Ryan","118111"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802562","Department for International Development","false","2017-12-12","<p>Our partnership with the Palestinian Authority includes a commitment from the Palestinian leadership to adhere to the principle of non-violence and to tackle language and avoid actions that could incite violence or hatred. The UK continues to urge the Palestinian leadership to uphold this principle. I raised the issue of incitement with senior Palestinian counterparts during my recent visit. The UK government strongly condemns all forms of violence and incitement to violence.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2017-12-12T18:12:35.74Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802562/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802562/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802562/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-12-07","Palestinians: Terrorism","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, pursuant to the Memorandum of Understanding between the Palestinian Authority (PA) and her Department, what discussions her Department has had with the PA on the distribution of diaries by Fatah’s youth movement at schools which pictured Abu Jihad who was responsible for the murder of 125 Israelis and Salah Khalaf who was the head of the terrorist organisation Black September.","true","Biography information for Joan Ryan","Enfield North","Joan Ryan","118112"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802563","Department for Education","false","2017-12-12","<p>The Chair of the Social Mobility Commission regularly engages with government Ministers, including through meetings which take place throughout the year. The Department for Education is fully committed to the work of the Social Mobility Commission. We value the wide-ranging work carried out by the Commission, including its research programme, its State of the Nation annual reports, and both the Social Mobility Index and the Social Mobility Employer Index. My Rt hon. Friend The Secretary of State spoke at the launch of the Social Mobility Employer Index in July 2017, alongside members of the Commission.</p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-12-12T17:44:45.08Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802563/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802563/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802563/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-12-07","Social Mobility Commission","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many meetings the Social Mobility Commission Commissioners held with Government Ministers in each of the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Lucy Powell","Manchester Central","Lucy Powell","118113"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802564","Department for International Development","false","2017-12-12","<p>Our partnership with the Palestinian Authority includes a commitment from the Palestinian leadership to adhere to the principle of non-violence and to tackle language and avoid actions that could incite violence or hatred. The UK continues to urge the Palestinian leadership to uphold this principle. I raised the issue of incitement with senior Palestinian counterparts during my recent visit. The UK government strongly condemns all forms of violence and incitement to violence.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2017-12-12T18:13:09.203Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802564/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802564/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802564/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-12-07","Palestinians: Overseas Aid","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, pursuant to the Memorandum of Understanding between the Palestinian Authority (PA) and her Department, what discussions her Department has had with the PA on its funding for summer camps in which children performed mock stabbing attacks.","true","Biography information for Joan Ryan","Enfield North","Joan Ryan","118114"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802565","Department for International Development","false","2017-12-14","<p>The UK Aid Strategy highlights the importance of combatting the world’s most serious diseases, including tuberculosis (TB). DFID provided (a) £10.6m in 2014/15 (b) £9.3m in 2015/16 and (c) £7m in 2016/17 for the development of drugs, diagnostics and vaccines to combat TB.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2017-12-14T10:27:59.887Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802565/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802565/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802565/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-12-07","Developing Countries: Tuberculosis","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what funding her Department provided for research and development for new drugs, diagnostics and vaccines for tuberculosis in the financial years (a) 2014-2015, (b) 2015-2016 and (c) 2016-2017.","false","Biography information for Mr Virendra Sharma","Ealing, Southall","Mr Virendra Sharma","118115"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802566","Department for International Development","false","2017-12-12","<p>Our partnership with the Palestinian Authority includes a commitment from the Palestinian leadership to adhere to the principle of non-violence and to tackle language and avoid actions that could incite violence or hatred. The UK continues to urge the Palestinian leadership to uphold this principle. I raised the issue of incitement with senior Palestinian counterparts during my recent visit. The UK government strongly condemns all forms of violence and incitement to violence.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2017-12-12T18:13:29.61Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802566/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802566/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802566/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-12-07","Palestinians: Terrorism","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, pursuant to the memorandum of understanding between the Palestinian Authority and her Department, what discussions her Department has had with the Palestinian Authority on the content of a music video broadcast on official Palestinian Authority TV on 10 April 2017 glorifying terror and promising to break the Jews.","true","Biography information for Joan Ryan","Enfield North","Joan Ryan","118116"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802567","Department for Education","false","2017-12-15","<p>The data on the numbers of children educated at home is not collected centrally.</p>","Guildford","Anne Milton",,"2017-12-15T13:23:02.32Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802567/answer","Biography information for Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802567/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802567/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-12-07","Home Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many pupils in (a) primary schools and (b) secondary schools entered into elective home education in each local authority in each of the last three years for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Layla Moran","Oxford West and Abingdon","Layla Moran","118117"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802568","Home Office","false","2017-12-11","<p>The Home Office does not collect this information. Decisions about how to deploy investigative resources are an operational matter for individual chief officers.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2017-12-11T15:42:24.433Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802568/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802568/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802568/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-12-07","Homicide","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what the cost to the public purse was of all murder investigations carried out by the police in the most recent 12-month period for which data is available.","false","Biography information for Julie Cooper","Burnley","Julie Cooper","118118"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802569","Attorney General","false","2017-12-20","<p>The following number of staff left the Attorney General’s Office (<strong>AGO), </strong>Government Legal Department (<strong>GLD</strong>) and HM Crown Prosecution Service Inspectorate<strong> (HMCPSI)</strong> during the period 1 January 2015 to 30 November 2017:</p><p>Attorney General’s Office 41</p><p>Government Legal Department 543</p><p>HM Crown Prosecution Service Inspectorate 18</p><p>Of these 602 moves, 266 were to other government departments.</p><p>During the period 1 January 2015 to 13 December 2017, 1,429 employees left the <strong>CPS</strong>.</p><p>The number of staff who have left the <strong>SFO</strong> since 2015 is as follows:</p><p>2015 72</p><p>2016 72</p><p>2017 64</p><p>The recording of nationality information within the AGO, GLD and HMCPSI is the responsibility of the individual to input via employee self-service. The information held relating to the above 602 moves is as follows:</p><ul><li><p>British 385</p></li><li><p>No declaration 205</p></li><li><p>Irish 2 (<em>taken to be Republic of Ireland as </em><em>Northern Irish is a separate option</em>)</p></li><li><p>Other nationality 10 (<em>the data held does not </em><em>distinguish between </em><em>EU and non-EU</em>)</p></li></ul><p>The <strong>CPS</strong> acts in accordance with guidance on the handling of this information and does not keep certificate information for any longer than is necessary once a recruitment (or other relevant) decision has been made. This is generally for a period of up to six months, to allow for the consideration and resolution of any disputes or complaints. The CPS is unable to confirm therefore how many of those members of staff who left during this period were nationals of non-UK EU countries.</p><p>As there is no legal requirement for employers to keep records on the nationality of staff, the <strong>SFO</strong> does not collate information on how many of these individuals were non-UK EU nationals.</p>","Kenilworth and Southam","Jeremy Wright",,"2017-12-20T17:23:12.99Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802569/answer","Biography information for Jeremy Wright","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802569/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802569/answer",,,,,"88","Attorney General","Attorney General","2017-12-07","Attorney General: Labour Turnover","1","House of Commons","To ask the Attorney General, how many members of staff have left the Law Officers' Departments since 1 January 2015; and how many of those members of staff were nationals of non-UK EU countries.","false","Biography information for Mrs Madeleine Moon","Bridgend","Mrs Madeleine Moon","118119"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802570","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-12-14","<p>​I refer the hon. Member to my answer of 20 October 2017 (PQ 107394).</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2017-12-14T15:53:59.917Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802570/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802570/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802570/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-12-07","Palestinians: Refugees","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what the Government's policy is on the right of return for Palestine refugees.","false","Biography information for Julie Cooper","Burnley","Julie Cooper","118120"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802571","Department of Health","false","2017-12-14","<p>The General Practice Forward View set out a package of investment in general practice, including reforms to increase capacity, such as recruitment and retention initiatives, extended access and the Time for Care programme.</p><p> </p><p>By 2020, the Government has committed to 5,000 additional doctors in general practice and 5,000 other staff in general practice; and by March 2019 everyone having improved access to general practitioner services, including sufficient routine appointments at evenings and weekends to meet locally determined demand.</p><p> </p><p>Kernow Clinical Commissioning Group (CCG) and the Devon CCGs that it borders are working collaboratively with NHS England, ensuring that CCG boundaries are not a barrier to improving patient care and providing a stable and sustainable platform for primary care.</p><p> </p><p>Local sharing of learning is taking place from progressive practices, such as St Austell Healthcare, where work at scale has seen the introduction of innovations such as the split of sites for on-the-day and ongoing care, access to a wider range of support staff and space for outpatient appointments.</p><p> </p><p>NHS England is also continuing to support projects through the Estates and Technology Transformation Fund (ETTF) to increase physical capacity and efficiency. Schemes include the expansion of Launceston Medical Centre in North Cornwall. A third party developer is progressing to an exchange on a strip of land behind the surgery for early in the new year, after which the practice will be able to take forward plans for an extension to the surgery (part-funded by a grant from the ETTF).</p><p> </p><p>There is a national NHS England scheme to recruit clinical pharmacists to general practice, so patients can get expert advice on medications. Five practices in the Truro area are among practices to benefit.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2017-12-14T14:15:35.217Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802571/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802571/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802571/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-12-07","General Practitioners: Cornwall","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what steps he is taking to increase capacity in general practice in (a) North Cornwall and (b) Cornwall.","false","Biography information for Scott Mann","North Cornwall","Scott Mann","118121"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802572","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-12-14","<p>Since April 1 2017, when data is available for BEIS, 280 members of staff have left the Department. The nationalities of staff that leave is not collated and to do so would incur disproportionate costs.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2017-12-14T11:31:39.883Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802572/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802572/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802572/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-12-07","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy: Labour Turnover","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, how many members of staff have left his Department since 1 January 2015; and how many of those members of staff were nationals of non-UK EU countries.","false","Biography information for Mrs Madeleine Moon","Bridgend","Mrs Madeleine Moon","118122"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802573","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-12-19","<p>The number of direct employees that have left the Department, for any reason, since January 2015 is 930.</p><p>The Department collects national identity data from its employees on a voluntary basis. Where staff self-describe their national identity as ‘other’ there is no requirement to provide further detail or evidence of their nationality. As such we are unable to determine the number of non-UK EU nationals that have left the Department during the time in question.</p><p>This is lower than the number that left in the last three years of Labour. Perhaps the Department has just become a more fulfilling place to work now we have a Government which faces up to problems, rather than making them worse.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2017-12-19T13:52:09.227Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802573/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802573/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802573/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-12-07","Department for Communities and Local Government: Labour Turnover","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how many members of staff have left his Department since 1 January 2015; and how many of those members of staff were nationals of non-UK EU countries.","false","Biography information for Mrs Madeleine Moon","Bridgend","Mrs Madeleine Moon","118123"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802574","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-12-15","<p>Since 1 January 2015, 358 staff have left the department (of which 53% was inter-Civil Service movement).</p><p>The Civil Service does not routinely collect information on the nationality of civil servants. The information requested is not held.</p><p> </p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2017-12-15T10:42:26.403Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802574/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802574/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802574/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2017-12-07","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport: Labour Turnover","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, how many members of staff have left her Department since 1 January 2015; and how many of those members of staff were nationals of non-UK EU countries.","false","Biography information for Mrs Madeleine Moon","Bridgend","Mrs Madeleine Moon","118124"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802575","Department for Education","false","2017-12-15","<p>1664 members of staff have left the department from 1 January 2015 to 30 November 2017.</p><p>The department does not hold nationality data for all staff. Evidence of nationality is checked at the point of recruitment into the Civil Service as part of wider pre-employment checks, but there is no requirement on departments to retain this information beyond the point at which it has served its purpose.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-12-15T14:54:15.577Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802575/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802575/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802575/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-12-07","Department for Education: Labour Turnover","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many members of staff have left her Department since 1 January 2015; and how many of those members of staff were nationals of non-UK EU countries.","false","Biography information for Mrs Madeleine Moon","Bridgend","Mrs Madeleine Moon","118125"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802576","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-12-14","<p>Since January 2015, 1070 staff on the payroll have left Defra. Of those, the recorded number of staff that have left the department in the same period, where non-UK EU nationality is known, is 36.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2017-12-14T15:43:44.64Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802576/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802576/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802576/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-12-07","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs: Labour Turnover","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, how many members of staff have left his Department since 1 January 2015; and how many of those members of staff were nationals of non-UK EU countries.","false","Biography information for Mrs Madeleine Moon","Bridgend","Mrs Madeleine Moon","118126"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802577","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-12-15","<p>The Department for Exiting the European Union’s monthly average attrition is 3.1% which equates to a quarterly figure of 8-9%. This level of attrition is not out of line with other Government departments, like the Cabinet Office, that operate a similar employment model. This figure includes the contractual exit of agency workers, secondees, contractors and fast streamers. The figure also includes a number of individuals who were on short-term loan from other Government Departments, brought in to aid in the establishment of DExEU.</p><p>Information on nationality cannot be released as individuals may be identifiable.</p>","Wycombe","Mr Steve Baker",,"2017-12-15T14:56:35.097Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802577/answer","Biography information for Mr Steve Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802577/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802577/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-12-07","Department for Exiting the European Union: Labour Turnover","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, how many members of staff have left his Department since its creation; and how many of those members of staff were nationals of non-UK EU countries.","false","Biography information for Mrs Madeleine Moon","Bridgend","Mrs Madeleine Moon","118127"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802578","Department for International Development","false","2017-12-14","<p>Since 1 January 2015, 530 staff have left DFID, of which 12 have declared as non-UK EU nationals.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2017-12-14T10:29:21.687Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802578/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802578/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802578/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-12-07","Department for International Development: Labour Turnover","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, how many members of staff have left her Department since 1 January 2015; and how many of those members of staff were nationals of non-UK EU countries.","false","Biography information for Mrs Madeleine Moon","Bridgend","Mrs Madeleine Moon","118128"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802579","Department for International Trade","false","2017-12-14","<p>In the period July 2016 to November 2017, a total of 195 UK based employees have left the Department for International Trade (DIT).</p><p>Since January 2015, there have been 144 leavers from UK Export Finance (UKEF).</p><p>The reasons for members of staff leaving include, amongst others, retiring, transferring departments, resignation and end of contract.</p><p>Neither DIT nor UKEF holds data on the nationalities of these staff.</p><p>Evidence of nationality is checked at the point of recruitment into the Civil Service as part of wider pre-employment checks, but there is no requirement on departments to retain this information beyond the point at which it has served its purpose.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands","118140","2017-12-14T13:40:47.777Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802579/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802579/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802579/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-12-07","Department for International Trade: Labour Turnover","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, how many members of staff have left his Department since it was created; and how many of those members of staff were nationals of non-UK EU countries.","false","Biography information for Mrs Madeleine Moon","Bridgend","Mrs Madeleine Moon","118129"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802580","Department for Transport","false","2017-12-15","<p>Including the central Department and the Executive Agencies, 5140 individuals have left since 1 January, 2015. Of those individuals, 31 can be confirmed as non-UK EU nationals.</p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2017-12-15T10:09:45.313Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802580/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802580/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802580/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-12-07","Department for Transport: Labour Turnover","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many members of staff have left his Department since 1 January 2015; and how many of those members of staff were nationals of non-UK EU countries.","false","Biography information for Mrs Madeleine Moon","Bridgend","Mrs Madeleine Moon","118130"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802581","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-12-14","<p>Since 1 January 2015, 24,889 individuals have left the Department.</p><p> </p><p>We do not know how many of these were nationals of non-UK EU countries. Evidence of nationality is checked at the point of recruitment into the Civil Service, as part of wider pre-employment checks. But, there is no requirement on departments to retain this information, beyond the point at which it has served its purpose.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2017-12-14T15:00:35.32Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802581/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802581/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802581/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-12-07","Department for Work and Pensions: Labour Turnover","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many members of staff have left his Department since 1 January 2015; and how many of those members of staff were nationals of non-UK EU countries.","false","Biography information for Mrs Madeleine Moon","Bridgend","Mrs Madeleine Moon","118131"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802582","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-12-14","<p>Between 1st January 2015 and 30th November 2017, 929 UK Based Staff have left the Foreign and Commonwealth Office (FCO). This includes retirement, resignation, career breaks and dismissal. It also includes civil servants returning to their parent department at the end of their loan/secondment.</p><p>The Aliens' Employment Act 1955 makes it a requirement that all UK Based Staff in the FCO must be British nationals or dual nationals where one of those nationalities is British. We do not centrally hold details of the nationality of our staff who are dual nationals.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2017-12-14T16:26:57.84Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802582/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802582/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802582/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-12-07","Foreign and Commonwealth Office: Labour Turnover","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, how many members of staff have left his Department since 1 January 2015; and how many of those members of staff were nationals of non-UK EU countries.","false","Biography information for Mrs Madeleine Moon","Bridgend","Mrs Madeleine Moon","118132"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802583","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-12-14","<p>I refer the hon. Member to my answer of 18 October 2017 (PQ 106847).</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2017-12-14T15:57:17.147Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802583/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802583/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802583/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-12-07","Israeli Settlements","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what the Government's policy is on Israeli settlement building in Jerusalem.","false","Biography information for Julie Cooper","Burnley","Julie Cooper","118133"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802584","Home Office","false","2017-12-14","<p>The number of people who have left the Home Office since 1 January 2015 is in the table (see attached). All Government Departments are bound by legal requirements concerning the right to work in the UK and, in addition, the Civil Service Nationality Rules.</p><p>Evidence of nationality is checked at the point of recruitment into the Civil Service as part of wider pre-employment checks, but there is no requirement on departments to retain this information beyond the point at which it has served its purpose.</p><p>More broadly, the Government will be consulting in due course on how we work with business to ensure that workers in this country have the skills that they need to get a job. But there are no proposals to publish lists of the number or proportion of foreign workers.</p>","Louth and Horncastle","Victoria Atkins",,"2017-12-14T17:05:35.893Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802584/answer","Biography information for Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802584/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802584/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-12-07","Home Office: Labour Turnover","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many members of staff have left her Department since 1 January 2015; and how many of those members of staff were nationals of non-UK EU countries.","false","Biography information for Mrs Madeleine Moon","Bridgend","Mrs Madeleine Moon","118134"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802585","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-12-14","<p>The following table shows the number of staff that have left the department since 1 January 2015. These figures include all leavers from the department, including (but not limited to) individuals whose contracts have ended, machinery of government transfers, dismissals, retirements, transfers to OGDs, voluntary and compulsory exits. They include leavers from the following business groups: MOJ HQ, HMPPS, HMCTS, LAA, OPG and CICA.</p><p> </p><p><strong>All MOJ Leavers 01.01.2015 to 30.09.2017</strong></p><p><strong> </strong></p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Period</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>MOJ</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>HMPPS</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Total</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>01.01.15 - 30.09.17</p></td><td><p>7,021</p></td><td><p>10,709</p></td><td><p><strong>17,730</strong></p></td></tr></tbody></table><p><strong> </strong></p><p>We are unable to calculate how many of these members of staff were nationals of non-UK EU countries as we do not hold data on employee’s nationality, and have no business requirement to do so.</p>","Bracknell","Dr Phillip Lee",,"2017-12-14T09:59:42.793Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802585/answer","Biography information for Dr Phillip Lee","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802585/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802585/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-12-07","Ministry of Justice: Labour Turnover","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many members of staff have left his Department since 1 January 2015; and how many of those members of staff were nationals of non-UK EU countries.","false","Biography information for Mrs Madeleine Moon","Bridgend","Mrs Madeleine Moon","118135"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802586","Northern Ireland Office","false","2017-12-18","<p>Since 1 January 2015 to date, 100 members of staff have left my department. Of these, 68 were due to loans or secondments ending and staff returning to their home department. 17 staff left through a voluntary exit scheme and 15 members of staff resigned or retired.</p><p> </p><p>We do not hold information in relation to how many of those staff were nationals of non-UK EU countries.</p><p> </p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2017-12-18T12:24:56.917Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802586/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802586/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802586/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2017-12-07","Northern Ireland Office: Labour Turnover","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, how many members of staff have left his Department since 1 January 2015; and how many of those members of staff were nationals of non-UK EU countries.","false","Biography information for Mrs Madeleine Moon","Bridgend","Mrs Madeleine Moon","118136"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802587","Scotland Office","false","2017-12-15","<p>The Scotland Office does not employ staff directly. Staff that join do so on assignment, loan or secondment from other government bodies, principally the Scottish Government and the Ministry of Justice, who remain the employers. 7 staff left the Scotland Office by resignation or retiral since 1 January 2015, details of the nationality of these staff are retained by the employing departments.</p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2017-12-15T14:33:28.633Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802587/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802587/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802587/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2017-12-07","Scotland Office: Labour Turnover","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, how many members of staff have left his Department since 1 January 2015; and how many of those members of staff were nationals of non-UK EU countries.","false","Biography information for Mrs Madeleine Moon","Bridgend","Mrs Madeleine Moon","118137"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802588","Wales Office","false","2017-12-14","<p>45 members of staff have left the Wales Office from 1 January 2015 to 7 December 2017. Of those, none were nationals of non-UK EU countries.</p>","Aberconwy","Guto Bebb",,"2017-12-14T16:15:47.787Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802588/answer","Biography information for Guto Bebb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802588/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802588/answer",,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2017-12-07","Wales Office: Labour Turnover","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, how many members of staff have left his Department since 1 January 2015; and how many of those members of staff were nationals of non-UK EU countries.","false","Biography information for Mrs Madeleine Moon","Bridgend","Mrs Madeleine Moon","118138"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802589","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-12-15","<p>As I set out in the Westminster Hall debate on 6 December the UK position on demolitions is clear: we consider them entirely unacceptable. In all but the most exceptional cases, they are contrary to international humanitarian law. Demolitions or evictions of Palestinian families from their homes cause unnecessary suffering and call into question Israel’s commitment to a viable two-state solution. The UK is particularly concerned by Israeli proposals to relocate the Bedouin population from the E1 area, which the UN has said could constitute forcible transfer.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2017-12-15T14:05:09.477Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802589/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802589/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802589/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-12-07","Occupied Territories: Demolition","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what the Government's policy is on the demolition of Palestinian buildings by Israel in the Occupied Palestinian Territories.","false","Biography information for Julie Cooper","Burnley","Julie Cooper","118139"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802590","Department for International Trade","false","2017-12-14","<p>In the period July 2016 to November 2017, a total of 195 UK based employees have left the Department for International Trade (DIT).</p><p>Since January 2015, there have been 144 leavers from UK Export Finance (UKEF).</p><p>The reasons for members of staff leaving include, amongst others, retiring, transferring departments, resignation and end of contract.</p><p>Neither DIT nor UKEF holds data on the nationalities of these staff.</p><p>Evidence of nationality is checked at the point of recruitment into the Civil Service as part of wider pre-employment checks, but there is no requirement on departments to retain this information beyond the point at which it has served its purpose.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands","118129","2017-12-14T13:40:47.837Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802590/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802590/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802590/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-12-07","UK Export Finance: Labour Turnover","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, how many members of staff have left UK Export Finance since 1 January 2015; and how many of those members of staff were nationals of non-UK EU countries.","false","Biography information for Mrs Madeleine Moon","Bridgend","Mrs Madeleine Moon","118140"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802591","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-12-15","<p>I refer the hon. Member to my answer of 20 November 2017 (PQ 113202).</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2017-12-15T13:51:42.147Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802591/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802591/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802591/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-12-07","Israel: Palestinians","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, whether the Government supports a two-state solution in Israel and Palestine.","false","Biography information for Julie Cooper","Burnley","Julie Cooper","118141"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802592","Department for International Development","false","2017-12-14","<p>The Government does not provide Official Development Assistance to the Israeli Defence Force relief mission in the Golan Heights.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2017-12-14T17:40:21.453Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802592/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802592/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802592/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-12-07","Israel Defense Forces","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, whether the Government provides Official Development Assistance to the Israeli Defence Force relief mission in the Golan Heights.","false","Biography information for Julie Cooper","Burnley","Julie Cooper","118142"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802593","Department for International Development","false","2017-12-14","<p>We are gravely concerned by the continued demolition of Palestinian property by the Israeli authorities. No structures directly funded by the UK in recent years have been demolished. A number of structures funded by the European Civil Protection and Humanitarian Aid Operations (ECHO) have been demolished in recent years. The UK’s financing share of EU expenditure varies year on year but has been approximately 15%. The UK regularly raises demolitions with the Government of Israel.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2017-12-14T17:40:55.557Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802593/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802593/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802593/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-12-07","Occupied Territories: Demolition","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, whether she plans to seek compensation for buildings and equipment demolished by Israel in the Occupied Palestine Territories which were funded by UK aid.","false","Biography information for Julie Cooper","Burnley","Julie Cooper","118143"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802594","Department for International Development","false","2017-12-14","<p>The UK is not providing the Government of Jordan with direct support to help with Palestinian refugees. However, the UK is a long-term supporter of the UN Relief and Works Agency for Palestine Refugees (UNRWA), which has a unique role to protect and provide essential services to over 5 million Palestinian refugees across the Middle East. In the current financial year, we will provide £38 million towards UNRWA’s Programme Budget, which will enable UNRWA to support Palestinian refugees across the region, including in Jordan. Additionally, the UK provides significant support to Jordan to improve education access and quality and create economic opportunities, which will benefit people throughout Jordan, including Palestinians.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2017-12-14T17:41:27.27Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802594/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802594/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802594/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-12-07","Palestinians: Refugees","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, whether her Department provides support to the Government of Jordan to help with Palestinian refugees to that country.","false","Biography information for Julie Cooper","Burnley","Julie Cooper","118144"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802595","Department for International Development","false","2017-12-14","<p>The UK is a long-term supporter of the UN Relief and Works Agency for Palestine Refugees (UNRWA) which has a unique role to protect and provide essential services to over 5 million Palestinian refugees across the Middle East. In financial year 2017/18 we will be provide £38 million towards UNRWA’s Programme Budget which will enable UNRWA to support Palestinian refugees across the region, including those from Gaza living in Jordan. Additionally, the UK provides significant support to Jordan to improve education access and quality and create economic opportunities, which will benefit people throughout Jordan, including Palestinians.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2017-12-14T17:42:03.197Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802595/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802595/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802595/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-12-07","Palestinians: Refugees","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what support the Government is providing to Palestinian refugees from Gaza living in Jordon.","false","Biography information for Julie Cooper","Burnley","Julie Cooper","118145"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802596","Department for International Development","false","2017-12-14","<p>The UK contributed £600,000 to the UN Relief and Works Agency for Palestine Refugees (UNRWA) 2017 Syria Emergency Appeal for Palestinian refugees from Syria in Jordan. Under the same grant, the UK also provided UNRWA with £1million of funding for their 2016 appeal in Jordan. UK funds have contributed to teacher salaries at UNRWA-run schools and have also been used to provide cash assistance for Palestinian refugees from Syria, that meet strict vulnerability criteria. Additionally, the UK provides significant support to Jordan to improve education access and quality and create economic opportunities, which will benefit people throughout Jordan, including Palestinians.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2017-12-14T17:42:41.16Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802596/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802596/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802596/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-12-07","Palestinians: Refugees","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what support the Government is providing to Palestinian refugees from Syria living in Jordan.","false","Biography information for Julie Cooper","Burnley","Julie Cooper","118146"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802597","Department for International Development","false","2017-12-14","<p>The UK is not providing the Government of Lebanon with direct support to help with Palestinian refugees. However, the UK is a long-term supporter of the UN Relief and Works Agency for Palestine Refugees (UNRWA) which has a unique role to protect and provide essential services to over 5 million Palestinian refugees across the Middle East. In the current financial year, we will provide £38 million towards UNRWA’s Programme Budget, which will enable UNRWA to support Palestinian refugees across the region, including in Lebanon.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2017-12-14T17:43:18.07Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802597/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802597/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802597/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-12-07","Palestinians: Refugees","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, whether her Department is providing official development assistant to the Government of Lebanon to help with Palestinian refugees.","false","Biography information for Julie Cooper","Burnley","Julie Cooper","118147"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802598","Department for International Trade","false","2017-12-15","<p>UK Export Finance (UKEF) publishes details of the companies it has supported on an annual basis in its Annual Report and Accounts which is presented to Parliament and on its website. These details include the type of project or export supported, and the destination country.</p><p><strong><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/uk-export-finance-annual-reports-and-accounts" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/uk-export-finance-annual-reports-and-accounts</a> </strong></p>","Wyre Forest","Mark Garnier",,"2017-12-15T14:37:43.503Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802598/answer","Biography information for Mark Garnier","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802598/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802598/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-12-07","Energy: Sub-Saharan Africa","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, what energy-related exports to sub-Saharan Africa have been supported by UK Export Finance and for which (a) companies (b) type of project or export (c) destination country in the most recent year for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Kerry McCarthy","Bristol East","Kerry McCarthy","118148"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802599","Department for International Trade","false","2017-12-15","<p>The Department for International Trade (DIT) uses multiple channels to provide support to UK companies looking for opportunities in the renewable energy sector in Africa. For example:</p><p>- UK Export Finance (UKEF), the UK’s export credit agency, has capacity to support UK trade and welcomes new applications for support from companies in the renewables sector. There is up to £2 billion available from UKEF for East Africa across all sectors. Further details on the products available from UKEF are listed on their website, along with country by country data. (<a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/uk-export-finance" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/uk-export-finance</a>).</p><p> </p><p>- In April 2016, UKEF also joined African Trade Insurance (ATI), the pan-African export credit agency. As an ATI member, UKEF gains access to information about upcoming opportunities for exporters. ATI will also provide a platform to raise awareness among project sponsors and buyers in African countries of the UKEF support available to importers of UK goods and services.</p><p> </p><p>- In 2016 UKEF signed a memorandum of understanding with the Kenyan government on renewables investment, to promote opportunities for private sector trade and investment by the UK in Kenya’s renewable energy sector.</p><p>- DIT has a High Value Campaign (HVC) targeting renewables exports to East Africa.</p><p> </p><p>- DIT also provides reactive support to exporters through our International Trade Advisor’s (ITA) network. (https://www.contactus.trade.gov.uk/office-finder/)</p>","Wyre Forest","Mark Garnier",,"2017-12-15T10:41:17.383Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802599/answer","Biography information for Mark Garnier","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802599/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802599/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-12-07","Renewable Energy: Africa","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, what support his Department provides to help UK renewable energy companies export to Africa.","false","Biography information for Kerry McCarthy","Bristol East","Kerry McCarthy","118149"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802600","House of Commons Commission","false","2017-12-13","<p>Parliament already has a single wireless network. However, this can appear to be a number of different ones when viewing the WiFi available on estate. This is due to it being segmented into a number of logical virtual networks. This is designed to enable effective cyber security management depending on the end user connecting. For example, guests on the Parliamentary Estate and users of non-Parliamentary devices computers are asked to manually enter an ID and password. However, Members and users of Parliamentary-issued devices automatically connect to the network. PDS plan to rationalise the number of WiFi networks visible on the Parliamentary estate over the course of 2018, the intent being to reduce the number visible to the minimum viable to meet cyber security requirements.</p>","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake",,"2017-12-13T12:50:30.023Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802600/answer","Biography information for Tom Brake","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802600/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802600/answer",,,,,"18","House of Commons Commission","House of Commons Commission","2017-12-07","Parliamentary Estate: WiFi","1","House of Commons","To ask the right hon. Member for Carshalton and Wallington, representing the House of Commons Commission, if the Commission will assess the potential merits of consolidating WiFi systems on the Parliamentary Estate.","false","Biography information for Dr David Drew","Stroud","Dr David Drew","118150"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802601","Department for Education","false","2017-12-15","<p>School governing boards should ensure that all schools develop a policy for supporting pupils with medical conditions that is reviewed regularly and is readily accessible to parents and school staff. The department does not hold information on individual diabetes episodes within schools, nor on the extent to which governing boards are making arrangements within their school policies for the support of pupils with medical conditions to give specific consideration to the needs of pupils with Type 1 Diabetes.</p><p> </p><p>Statutory guidance on supporting pupils at school with medical conditions includes information for schools on developing school policies. We have also provided a collection of links to useful resources to help schools support their pupils with medical conditions. This includes links to the Juvenile Diabetes Research Foundation / East of England Children and Young People Diabetes Network; and to Diabetes UK website, which includes a sample medical conditions policy.</p><p> </p><p>Ofsted’s Common Inspection Framework requires inspectors, in making judgements upon schools, to pay particular attention to the outcomes of a range of groups of pupils, including those with medical needs. Ofsted included guidance to inspectors on this matter in their March 2017 school inspection update, reminding inspectors that they should consider how schools are meeting the needs of pupils with medical conditions. The content of inspection frameworks and training of inspectors are matters for Her Majesty’s Chief Inspector.</p><p> </p><p>Governing boards must make reasonable adjustments to ensure that disabled children and young people are not at a substantial disadvantage compared with their peers. This duty is anticipatory: adjustments must be planned and put in place in advance, to prevent that disadvantage.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","118152 ; 118153 