"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802720","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-12-12","<p>Work is the best route out of poverty, and Universal Credit supports parents to move into and progress in work, and raises the income of families.</p><p> </p><p>Since 2010 the number of children growing up in households where no one works has fallen by half a million.</p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2017-12-12T13:14:01.697Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802720/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802720/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802720/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-12-07","Universal Credit: Glasgow North East","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what steps he is taking to ensure that the roll-out of universal credit in Glasgow North East constituency will not result in an increase in child poverty.","false","Biography information for Mr Paul Sweeney","Glasgow North East","Mr Paul Sweeney","118269"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802721","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-12-14","<p>At present, there are 21 officers and 268 soldiers based at Hyde Park Barracks. This includes personnel that are permanently based at Hyde Park Barracks for duty purposes, but does not include personnel that reside at Hyde Park Barracks but work elsewhere.</p><p>Figures are single service estimates and not produced by official statistics.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2017-12-14T17:19:33.573Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802721/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802721/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802721/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-12-07","Hyde Park Barracks","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many (a) officers and (b) soldiers are currently based at Hyde Park Barracks.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","118270"
